          "type": "accordion_pane",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Why do swimmers/surfers wear one-piece swimsuits?",
            "content": "<p>They are perfect for water sports.  Whether you're an avid swimmer or surfer – one-piece swim suits offer the best peace of mind. This style means you don't have to contend with pesky straps which may fall as you engage in some serious water sport activity.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_pane_aKDwW9": {
          "type": "accordion_pane",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Is a one-piece swimsuit more flattering?",
            "content": "<p>One-piece swimsuits can be flattering for many body types. They can provide support and coverage in all the right places.  Ultimately, the most important thing is to choose a swimsuit that makes you feel comfortable and confident.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_pane_3WeXrq": {
          "type": "accordion_pane",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is UPF swimwear?",
            "content": "<p>UPF (or Ultraviolet Protection Factor) swimwear is swimwear that offers protection from the sun's UVA and UVB rays. UPF relates to protection from clothing whilst SPF relates to sunscreen.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_pane_QeqwUA": {
          "type": "accordion_pane",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What do you wear under a surf suit?",
            "content": "<p>With our one piece swimsuits, you don’t need to wear anything underneath! The cut is designed to be super supportive to hold you in.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_pane_4UD7yC": {
          "type": "accordion_pane",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Will the white colour be transparent when wet?",
            "content": "<p>We double line all of our swimsuits, and our white suits are lined with a skin colour fabric to prevent them from becoming transparent.</p>"
          }
        }
